---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
import TopicHero from "../components/TopicHero.astro"
import TopicNav from "../components/TopicNav.astro"
import Figure from "../components/Figure.astro"
import Gallery from "../components/Gallery.astro"

import g01 from "../assets/images/gallery-01.png"
import g12 from "../assets/images/gallery-12.png"
import conservationHero from "../assets/images/conservation-hero.png"

const threats = [
  { label: "Habitat degradation", text: "Overgrazing, mining, and infrastructure fragment the steppe and erode the prey base the cat depends on." },
  { label: "Prey poisoning", text: "Programs to poison pikas and rodents as pests remove the manul's primary food and can poison cats directly." },
  { label: "Hunting & trapping", text: "Historically hunted for its fur and still caught in traps set for other animals, or killed by herders' dogs." },
  { label: "Climate pressure", text: "Shifting weather patterns alter prey cycles and snow conditions across a range already defined by extremes." },
]

const efforts = [
  { label: "IUCN status", text: "Listed as Least Concern since 2020 after better survey data, but with a population trend assessed as declining." },
  { label: "Legal protection", text: "Protected across much of its range and listed on CITES Appendix II, restricting international trade." },
  { label: "Research alliances", text: "Coordinated field studies — notably the Pallas's Cat International Conservation Alliance — fill critical knowledge gaps." },
  { label: "Ex-situ programs", text: "Zoos worldwide maintain careful breeding and health programs to safeguard genetic diversity and study the species." },
]

const gallery = [
  { src: conservationHero.src, alt: "A lone Pallas's cat on a ridge at golden hour", caption: "Naturally sparse and hard to count, the manul is easy to overlook in conservation planning." },
  { src: g01.src, alt: "A Pallas's cat in snow", caption: "Cold-adapted and range-restricted, with little room to shift as conditions change." },
  { src: g12.src, alt: "A Pallas's cat in autumn grassland", caption: "Healthy steppe and intact prey populations are the foundation of its future." },
]
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Conservation — The Manul Atlas"
  description="Threats facing the Pallas's cat, its IUCN status, and the global effort to protect it."
  image={conservationHero.src}
>
  <TopicHero
    eyebrow="Chapter 06 · Conservation"
    title="Protecting a cat we barely see"
    intro="Naturally rare, widely scattered, and notoriously difficult to study, the manul presents one of the harder puzzles in small-cat conservation."
    image={conservationHero.src}
    imageAlt="A lone Pallas's cat overlooking a vast steppe at golden hour"
  />

  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 lg:px-0">
    <div class="prose-editorial">
      <p>
        The Pallas's cat is currently classified as Least Concern by the IUCN, a status updated in 2020 after
        expanded surveys revealed the species was more widespread than once feared. That label, however, comes with
        an important caveat: the overall population trend is assessed as <em>declining</em>. The cat's natural
        rarity and vast, remote range make accurate counts extremely difficult, and local populations can vanish
        without ever being recorded.
      </p>
      <p>
        The pressures are largely indirect. The manul is rarely targeted on purpose today, but it suffers from the
        cumulative effects of human activity across the steppe — degraded grassland, poisoned prey, incidental
        trapping, and predation by domestic and herding dogs. For a low-density specialist, even modest losses can
        tip a local population toward collapse.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="my-12">
      <Figure
        src={conservationHero.src}
        alt="A solitary Pallas's cat on a rocky ridge at sunset"
        caption="Conserving the manul means conserving the steppe itself: its prey, its burrow-digging neighbors, and the wide, intact landscapes that a low-density predator needs to persist."
        ratio="16/10"
      />
    </div>

    <h2 class="mb-6 font-serif text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Key threats</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-[var(--radius-card)] border border-line bg-line sm:grid-cols-2">
      {threats.map((t) => (
        <div class="bg-parchment-2 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-ink">{t.label}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">{t.text}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h2 class="mb-6 mt-12 font-serif text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">What is being done</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-[var(--radius-card)] border border-line bg-line sm:grid-cols-2">
      {efforts.map((e) => (
        <div class="bg-parchment-2 p-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-ink">{e.label}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">{e.text}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="prose-editorial mt-12">
      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">A future on the steppe</h2>
      <p>
        Protecting the Pallas's cat is, in practice, about protecting the whole steppe ecosystem. Safeguarding pika
        and rodent populations, limiting poisoning campaigns, maintaining intact grassland, and reducing incidental
        trapping all benefit the manul alongside countless other species. International research collaborations
        continue to close basic gaps in our knowledge — from population size to disease ecology — that are
        essential to managing the species well.
      </p>
      <p>
        For now, the manul endures across a huge sweep of Asia, hidden in plain sight among the rocks. Keeping it
        there will depend on sustained attention to a cat that, by its very nature, does everything it can not to
        be noticed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 lg:px-8">
    <Gallery images={gallery} columns={3} />
  </section>

  <TopicNav current="/conservation" />
  <div class="h-10"></div>
</BaseLayout>
